President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Adam Gamoran is nominated for the Board of Directors of the National Board for Education Sciences. He is currently the John D. MacArthur Professor of Sociology and Educational Policy Studies at the University of Wisconsin-Madison. Judith D. Singer is nominated for the same position. She is currently the Senior Vice Provost for Faculty Development and Diversity at Harvard University. James Timberlake is nominated for the Board of Directors of the National Institute of Building Sciences. He is a founding partner of the KieranTimberlake architecture firm and teaches at the University of Pennsylvania's School of Design.